\parai{Refinability} speaks of the ability to apply edits to improve the quality of information returned in future. Incomplete or incorrect results from a KG or an SE are likely due to missing or erroneous input, which can be addressed by a user with write privileges. Refining LLMs in order to remove an erroneous result or address an incomplete answer is more indirect at best and infeasible at worst. 
 The indirect way is to identify the troublesome text(s) in the training corpora, edit or remove them, and re-run the entire training and fine-tuning process. 
 However, there is no guarantee that even this will fix the issue, as the questionable output may stem from multiple pieces mashed together in the generative process.
 Without re-training the LLM, fixing errors is non-trivial. Despite some works pursuing parameter-weight editing for the latent model, there is no principled way of ensuring the desired effects.